1
00:01:09,567 --> 00:01:10,467
Please...

2
00:01:11,367 --> 00:01:12,167
Please...

3
00:01:14,117 --> 00:01:16,117
The customer is not
answering the phone...

4
00:01:19,087 --> 00:01:19,947
[ 911 ]

5
00:01:24,937 --> 00:01:27,767
It's 144-2 Seonjinro.

6
00:01:27,767 --> 00:01:29,427
I think someone passed out.

7
00:01:29,427 --> 00:01:30,967
Please hurry.

8
00:01:30,967 --> 00:01:33,297
144-2 Seonjinro?

9
00:01:33,297 --> 00:01:34,687
Yes, we'll be right there.

10
00:01:34,687 --> 00:01:37,507
What's the condition
of the one who passed out?

11
00:01:37,507 --> 00:01:39,827
- I don't know.
- Pardon?

12
00:01:39,827 --> 00:01:41,107
What did you say?

13
00:01:42,347 --> 00:01:44,267
I said I don't know!

14
00:01:44,267 --> 00:01:48,267
He doesn't know
if he's in pain or not!

15
00:01:48,267 --> 00:01:50,127
[ Kang Shi Young ]

16
00:01:57,397 --> 00:02:00,067
He's a CIPA patient.

17
00:02:00,067 --> 00:02:02,997
He may have collapsed
due to a high fever.

18
00:02:02,997 --> 00:02:04,777
Please take the ice packs,

19
00:02:04,777 --> 00:02:07,377
and check his temperature
as soon as you find him.

20
00:02:27,247 --> 00:02:30,357
Where is Dr. Cha,
I mean, Mr. Cha Yo Han?

21
00:02:30,357 --> 00:02:31,587
This way.

22
00:02:33,457 --> 00:02:34,767
Over here.

23
00:02:39,687 --> 00:02:42,067
Dr. Cha, are you okay?

24
00:02:43,887 --> 00:02:45,417
I'm fine.

25
00:02:45,417 --> 00:02:48,827
- What happened to your...
- I fell.

26
00:02:49,927 --> 00:02:51,807
What else? A fever?

27
00:03:00,257 --> 00:03:02,027
You have a fever.

28
00:03:02,027 --> 00:03:05,177
Aside from that, did they
run any other tests?

29
00:03:05,177 --> 00:03:08,167
That's all. No other issues.

30
00:03:09,227 --> 00:03:10,737
What about Ki Seok's results?

31
00:03:10,737 --> 00:03:12,977
As you said, an abscess was found,

32
00:03:12,977 --> 00:03:14,967
so we started
administering antibiotics.

33
00:03:14,967 --> 00:03:16,417
You did?

34
00:03:16,417 --> 00:03:19,217
Dr. Kang was calling
to tell you that,

35
00:03:19,217 --> 00:03:21,117
then reported when
you didn't pick up.

36
00:03:21,117 --> 00:03:22,837
We were so scared.

37
00:03:24,897 --> 00:03:27,247
How is Ki Seok's condition?

38
00:03:27,247 --> 00:03:28,757
Never mind.

39
00:03:28,757 --> 00:03:31,337
Let's get going.
We can talk on the way.

40
00:03:32,467 --> 00:03:33,467
No.

41
00:03:34,467 --> 00:03:36,467
Not until your fever goes down.

42
00:03:37,837 --> 00:03:40,487
Don't think of just
laughing this off.

43
00:04:01,417 --> 00:04:04,447
[ Doctor John ]
[ Episode 14: A certain choice ]

44
00:04:17,187 --> 00:04:18,597
Excuse me for a minute.

45
00:04:30,077 --> 00:04:32,217
How is the patient?

46
00:04:32,217 --> 00:04:35,967
We need his phlegm test
results to be sure,

47
00:04:35,967 --> 00:04:38,067
but the abscess found in his MRI

48
00:04:38,067 --> 00:04:41,567
is consistent with nocardiosis,
so he's currently on antibiotics.

49
00:04:41,567 --> 00:04:43,167
[ Nocardiosis: Disease common in people
with weakened immune systems ]

50
00:04:48,407 --> 00:04:49,927
Where is Dr. Cha?

51
00:04:49,927 --> 00:04:51,477
He's not at the hospital.

52
00:04:51,477 --> 00:04:53,557
He's been excluded
from the treatments.

53
00:04:56,577 --> 00:04:59,607
Dr. Cha provided the
diagnosis, right?

54
00:05:00,837 --> 00:05:02,107
Is that right?

55
00:05:04,577 --> 00:05:05,987
Yes, he did.

56
00:05:07,027 --> 00:05:08,977
He is an amazing man.

57
00:05:14,367 --> 00:05:15,407
Yes.

58
00:05:16,457 --> 00:05:19,147
The Ethics Committee
made its decision.

59
00:05:19,147 --> 00:05:21,157
Let's take care of
Dr. Cha issue first,

60
00:05:21,157 --> 00:05:24,157
then suspend life
prolongation for Chairman.

61
00:05:26,067 --> 00:05:28,667
[ Decision by the Ethics Committee ]

62
00:05:28,667 --> 00:05:32,567
[ Based on the medical condition of the
patient, it's legitimate to suspend... ]

63
00:05:37,107 --> 00:05:38,907
Dr. Cha...

64
00:05:38,907 --> 00:05:42,237
I feel it'd be a shame to lose him.

65
00:05:42,237 --> 00:05:44,007
Even after he left the hospital,

66
00:05:44,007 --> 00:05:46,507
he focused on
Lee Ki Seok's diagnosis.

67
00:05:48,987 --> 00:05:50,207
So?

68
00:05:51,167 --> 00:05:52,947
The Chairman...

69
00:05:52,947 --> 00:05:55,897
had wanted to
cultivate great doctors.

70
00:05:55,967 --> 00:05:59,267
I wonder if we're perhaps
going against his wish in this.

71
00:06:00,267 --> 00:06:03,267
To me, Dr. Cha seems like
a ticking time bomb literally.

72
00:06:03,317 --> 00:06:05,857
Our hospital has been
chaotic ever since he came.

73
00:06:05,857 --> 00:06:06,987
And also,

74
00:06:06,987 --> 00:06:10,007
will you be okay with this
chaotic environment?

75
00:06:10,007 --> 00:06:12,327
We must put this issue away first

76
00:06:12,327 --> 00:06:14,527
in order to move
onto the next one.

77
00:06:28,497 --> 00:06:29,757
Let's go.

78
00:06:29,757 --> 00:06:31,437
I'm really okay now.

79
00:06:31,437 --> 00:06:32,647
Let's go, Kang Shi Young.

80
00:06:38,087 --> 00:06:40,947
Aigoo, why isn't he calling?

81
00:06:42,957 --> 00:06:44,257
That's him.

82
00:06:44,257 --> 00:06:45,947
Hang on a sec.
[ Lee Yoo Joon ]

83
00:06:54,237 --> 00:06:56,457
It's best if we don't let on.

84
00:07:00,627 --> 00:07:02,067
Dr. Cha.

85
00:07:02,067 --> 00:07:04,007
Dr. Cha, can you see okay?

86
00:07:04,007 --> 00:07:05,747
Yes, I can see.

87
00:07:10,087 --> 00:07:11,267
Ki Seok.

88
00:07:11,267 --> 00:07:13,137
It's Dr. Cha. Do you see him?

89
00:07:15,787 --> 00:07:17,317
Ki Seok.

90
00:07:18,627 --> 00:07:20,177
How are you? Are you okay?

91
00:07:20,177 --> 00:07:23,257
If you're okay,
blink your eyes once.

92
00:07:28,727 --> 00:07:31,157
You'll start recovering slowly.

93
00:07:31,157 --> 00:07:33,217
Once your pneumonia goes away,

94
00:07:33,217 --> 00:07:35,527
it'll be easier for you to breathe,

95
00:07:35,527 --> 00:07:38,007
then we'll remove the ventilator.

96
00:07:38,007 --> 00:07:39,317
After that,

97
00:07:39,317 --> 00:07:41,717
you'll be moving your
hands and feet,

98
00:07:43,037 --> 00:07:46,487
and be able to turn
your head as well.

99
00:07:53,167 --> 00:07:54,867
Thank you, Lee Ki Seok.

100
00:07:57,437 --> 00:07:59,477
You must've been scared,

101
00:07:59,477 --> 00:08:01,107
yet you endured it.

102
00:08:10,877 --> 00:08:12,207
Stay strong.

103
00:08:13,637 --> 00:08:16,287
Stay strong, so the
next time we meet,

104
00:08:16,287 --> 00:08:18,497
you'll be your healthy self.

105
00:08:18,497 --> 00:08:19,907
You got it?

106
00:08:25,267 --> 00:08:28,047
Fighting, Lee Ki Seok.

107
00:08:28,047 --> 00:08:29,747
Fighting!

108
00:08:47,877 --> 00:08:50,147
You're asking why isn't
Dr. Cha coming?

109
00:08:54,797 --> 00:08:56,637
He'll come.

110
00:08:56,667 --> 00:08:58,067
He will, but...

111
00:08:59,067 --> 00:09:01,167
it'll take a little time.

112
00:09:26,517 --> 00:09:28,147
Doesn't it hurt?

113
00:09:31,727 --> 00:09:33,337
Why would I be hurting?

114
00:09:34,407 --> 00:09:35,617
You know I don't.

115
00:09:36,847 --> 00:09:38,647
You look like you're hurting.

116
00:09:39,637 --> 00:09:40,777
Is that right?

117
00:09:42,467 --> 00:09:44,567
You can say you're hurting.

118
00:09:45,567 --> 00:09:46,937
Please say it hurts.

119
00:09:46,937 --> 00:09:48,667
Why always say you're okay...

120
00:09:51,167 --> 00:09:52,757
It's hard, huh?

121
00:09:54,857 --> 00:09:57,637
You're always worried about me...

122
00:09:57,637 --> 00:09:59,457
and you're anxious.

123
00:10:00,807 --> 00:10:03,237
Because I'm your guardian, Dr. Cha.

124
00:10:04,557 --> 00:10:06,577
It's my duty.

125
00:10:10,667 --> 00:10:12,087
Let's go back now.

126
00:10:15,637 --> 00:10:16,717
Kang Shi Young.

127
00:10:21,277 --> 00:10:22,637
Thank you.

128
00:10:30,757 --> 00:10:33,297
You told me before that

129
00:10:33,297 --> 00:10:35,897
if you quit being a doctor...

130
00:10:35,897 --> 00:10:39,277
you'd have no idea
what else to do.

131
00:10:39,277 --> 00:10:41,667
I realized it just now.

132
00:10:41,667 --> 00:10:44,537
You'll have to treat patients
for the rest of your life.

133
00:10:45,567 --> 00:10:48,067
No other work would suit you.

134
00:10:48,127 --> 00:10:50,457
So please don't be sick.

135
00:10:52,267 --> 00:10:59,687
♫ Like a disappearing shadow ♫

136
00:10:59,687 --> 00:11:04,907
♫ I couldn’t approach you ♫

137
00:11:06,517 --> 00:11:14,517
♫ I'm afraid of even a small flutter ♫

138
00:11:14,517 --> 00:11:21,387
♫ I've lost my way,
but you came to me ♫

139
00:11:21,387 --> 00:11:27,337
♫ And you took my hand in yours ♫

140
00:11:27,337 --> 00:11:33,757
♫ You’ve made me live again ♫

141
00:11:33,757 --> 00:11:37,437
♫ To say that I love you ♫

142
00:11:37,437 --> 00:11:40,657
♫ That I miss you ♫

143
00:11:41,587 --> 00:11:48,837
♫ It was like a dream to be with you ♫

144
00:11:48,837 --> 00:11:52,257
♫ That I love you ♫

145
00:11:52,257 --> 00:11:56,457
♫ And I miss you ♫

146
00:11:56,457 --> 00:12:00,677
♫ I can no longer say
these words ♫

147
00:12:00,677 --> 00:12:06,177
♫ Even though it hurts, you're
my reason for happiness ♫

148
00:12:08,567 --> 00:12:14,667
♫ All of my memories
are filled with you ♫

149
00:12:14,677 --> 00:12:20,487
♫ Even if I can't erase it ♫

150
00:12:20,487 --> 00:12:24,727
♫ To say that I love you ♫

151
00:12:25,647 --> 00:12:28,347
♫ To say that I miss you ♫

152
00:12:29,867 --> 00:12:36,767
♫ It was like a dream to be with you ♫

153
00:12:36,777 --> 00:12:40,407
♫ That I love you ♫

154
00:12:40,407 --> 00:12:44,367
♫ That I miss you ♫

155
00:12:44,367 --> 00:12:48,877
♫ I can no longer say
these words ♫

156
00:12:48,877 --> 00:12:53,407
♫ Even though it hurts, you're
my reason for happiness ♫

157
00:12:53,407 --> 00:12:55,717
Don't get sick without
my permission.

158
00:13:18,327 --> 00:13:22,317
[ Seoul Hansae Hospital ]

159
00:13:22,317 --> 00:13:24,787
[ Pain Management Center ]

160
00:13:24,787 --> 00:13:26,127
That's doesn't make sense.

161
00:13:26,127 --> 00:13:28,227
How can he treat patients
if he can't feel pain?

162
00:13:28,227 --> 00:13:30,587
- A CIPA patient?
- Dr. Cha has a disease.

163
00:13:30,587 --> 00:13:32,787
Look here, it says
he's a CIPA patient.

164
00:13:32,787 --> 00:13:34,337
He's unable to feel pain?

165
00:13:34,337 --> 00:13:36,117
It was on "Famous Healers."

166
00:13:37,037 --> 00:13:39,957
- So he really can't feel pain?
- Is this true?

167
00:13:49,487 --> 00:13:51,907
Ki Seok's phlegm culture
test results are out.

168
00:13:51,907 --> 00:13:52,907
It's confirmed.

169
00:13:52,907 --> 00:13:54,047
You heard, right?

170
00:13:54,067 --> 00:13:55,067
Yes.

171
00:13:56,167 --> 00:13:57,757
Dr. Cha.

172
00:13:57,757 --> 00:13:59,667
Is he doing okay?

173
00:13:59,697 --> 00:14:02,477
He said he'll stay home and rest.

174
00:14:02,477 --> 00:14:06,517
Isn't Dr. Cha Yo Han
seeing patients today?

175
00:14:06,517 --> 00:14:07,547
No.

176
00:14:07,547 --> 00:14:09,417
He won't be seeing
patients for a while.

177
00:14:09,417 --> 00:14:11,007
Why all of a sudden?

178
00:14:11,007 --> 00:14:13,927
I came all the way
from the countryside.

179
00:14:13,927 --> 00:14:16,497
I heard that Dr. Cha is ill.

180
00:14:16,497 --> 00:14:17,757
Is it true?

181
00:14:17,757 --> 00:14:19,547
But how?

182
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:21,967
He's unable to feel any pain.

183
00:14:21,967 --> 00:14:24,687
That, congenital
insensitive something...

184
00:14:24,687 --> 00:14:26,267
You're done, sir.

185
00:14:26,317 --> 00:14:28,367
Please wait outside,
and we'll call you.

186
00:14:28,367 --> 00:14:29,437
Thank you.

187
00:14:29,437 --> 00:14:30,777
I see, okay.

188
00:14:30,777 --> 00:14:33,577
Please change in to
your patient's gown.

189
00:14:34,967 --> 00:14:36,267
Here you go.

190
00:14:47,107 --> 00:14:48,807
What? What is it?

191
00:14:48,807 --> 00:14:50,337
It's tomorrow.

192
00:14:50,337 --> 00:14:51,867
The disciplinary committee
for Dr. Cha.

193
00:14:51,867 --> 00:14:52,917
What?

194
00:14:52,917 --> 00:14:54,747
Is it really tomorrow?

195
00:14:54,747 --> 00:14:56,087
So soon?

196
00:14:56,087 --> 00:14:57,547
I know.

197
00:14:57,547 --> 00:14:59,717
I think his punishment
will be harsh.

198
00:14:59,717 --> 00:15:02,547
Is it this easy to
dismiss someone?

199
00:15:02,547 --> 00:15:05,707
If he damaged the hospital's
reputation, then yes.

200
00:15:05,707 --> 00:15:08,227
Image is the most
important thing to them.

201
00:15:08,227 --> 00:15:09,807
Then what should we do?

202
00:15:09,807 --> 00:15:12,197
Do we just standby and
watch Dr. Cha leave?

203
00:15:13,497 --> 00:15:15,067
Yes, Dr. Cha.

204
00:15:15,067 --> 00:15:16,917
You received the notice, right?

205
00:15:16,917 --> 00:15:18,067
It's tomorrow.

206
00:15:18,067 --> 00:15:19,717
I don't have to attend, right?

207
00:15:19,767 --> 00:15:21,867
Even if you don't, the disciplinary
committee will hold.

208
00:15:21,867 --> 00:15:24,367
[ Notice of attendance ]
But if you don't attend,
you can't defend yourself.

209
00:15:24,427 --> 00:15:25,547
Are you okay with that?

210
00:15:25,547 --> 00:15:27,177
Yes, I'm fine.

211
00:15:27,177 --> 00:15:28,587
Okay then.

212
00:15:28,587 --> 00:15:29,887
I'll call you.

213
00:15:29,887 --> 00:15:31,367
Also...

214
00:15:33,817 --> 00:15:36,177
do you have time today?

215
00:15:36,177 --> 00:15:37,227
Today?

216
00:15:37,227 --> 00:15:39,737
There's someone
I'd like for you to meet.

217
00:15:41,147 --> 00:15:44,547
You asked me who recommended
you to the hospital, correct?

218
00:15:44,547 --> 00:15:45,937
He's the one.

219
00:15:52,907 --> 00:15:54,227
Hello.

220
00:15:54,227 --> 00:15:55,967
Mr. Yang Jae Young,
how are you feeling?

221
00:15:55,967 --> 00:15:57,897
Is it true?

222
00:15:57,897 --> 00:16:02,077
That Dr. Cha is really
unable to feel any pain?

223
00:16:02,077 --> 00:16:04,237
- Yes.
- My God.

224
00:16:04,237 --> 00:16:05,937
How can this be...

225
00:16:05,937 --> 00:16:08,467
I had no idea that

226
00:16:08,467 --> 00:16:10,417
he was like that.

227
00:16:10,417 --> 00:16:11,927
Yes, yes.

228
00:16:11,927 --> 00:16:14,597
Dr. Cha has CIPA.

229
00:16:14,597 --> 00:16:15,777
But...

230
00:16:15,777 --> 00:16:17,967
who treated your neuralgia, sir?

231
00:16:17,967 --> 00:16:19,207
Dr. Cha, right?

232
00:16:19,207 --> 00:16:20,957
He's such a competent doctor...

233
00:16:20,957 --> 00:16:22,887
That's what I'm saying.

234
00:16:22,887 --> 00:16:25,747
I couldn't even open my mouth,

235
00:16:25,747 --> 00:16:27,827
so I couldn't eat properly.

236
00:16:27,827 --> 00:16:29,307
I couldn't speak either,

237
00:16:29,307 --> 00:16:31,487
and suffered immensely.

238
00:16:31,487 --> 00:16:32,697
I mean,

239
00:16:32,697 --> 00:16:34,667
he does not know pain,

240
00:16:34,667 --> 00:16:36,647
but how does he cure it so well?

241
00:16:37,667 --> 00:16:40,267
That man deserves an award.

242
00:16:41,457 --> 00:16:44,227
So when will Dr. Cha
be returning?

243
00:16:44,227 --> 00:16:47,877
I'd really like to thank him.

244
00:16:49,187 --> 00:16:51,227
I'm the grateful one, sir.

245
00:16:51,227 --> 00:16:52,847
Thank you so much!

246
00:16:54,137 --> 00:16:56,427
Everyone, gather here. Hurry.

247
00:17:06,307 --> 00:17:08,247
I think there is a way
to help Dr. Cha.

248
00:17:08,247 --> 00:17:09,087
But how?

249
00:17:09,087 --> 00:17:10,577
- Really?
- What is it?

250
00:17:12,107 --> 00:17:14,917
Starting now, we'll split into
two teams and proceed.

251
00:17:15,767 --> 00:17:21,067
♫ I'm sure everything
will get better ♫

252
00:17:21,127 --> 00:17:24,107
♫ The more I get to know you ♫

253
00:17:24,107 --> 00:17:27,187
♫ You warm my heart ♫

254
00:17:27,187 --> 00:17:29,827
♫ We must never try to stop ♫

255
00:17:29,827 --> 00:17:32,437
Please read this over.

256
00:17:32,437 --> 00:17:36,067
♫ I can't erase you from
deep inside my heart ♫

257
00:17:36,067 --> 00:17:38,607
Really? Okay, thank you.

258
00:17:38,607 --> 00:17:39,927
Yes, I understand.

259
00:17:39,927 --> 00:17:41,197
Okay.

260
00:18:12,937 --> 00:18:14,517
Minister.

261
00:18:14,517 --> 00:18:16,407
Dr. Cha is here.

262
00:18:27,217 --> 00:18:28,737
Hello, sir.

263
00:18:28,737 --> 00:18:30,377
I'm Cha Yo Han.

264
00:18:30,377 --> 00:18:33,207
I've been wanting to meet you.

265
00:18:33,207 --> 00:18:35,037
Have a seat.

266
00:18:36,437 --> 00:18:37,417
Have a seat.

267
00:18:53,957 --> 00:18:55,467
So...

268
00:18:55,467 --> 00:18:57,697
why did you want to see me?

269
00:18:57,697 --> 00:19:01,157
At first, it wasn't for the patients,

270
00:19:01,157 --> 00:19:03,907
but probably to know
more about your illness.

271
00:19:03,907 --> 00:19:06,277
That's why you became
a doctor, correct?

272
00:19:08,137 --> 00:19:10,487
I also felt the same way.

273
00:19:11,367 --> 00:19:14,167
I wanted to know more
about this disease

274
00:19:14,167 --> 00:19:17,667
which hardens the muscles
and the organs gradually.

275
00:19:17,667 --> 00:19:19,967
I tried to find a way to

276
00:19:19,967 --> 00:19:22,067
cure this disease.

277
00:19:22,097 --> 00:19:25,277
However, I couldn't do it.

278
00:19:25,277 --> 00:19:29,217
Instead, I found another way.

279
00:19:30,527 --> 00:19:32,697
A way to resolve the

280
00:19:32,697 --> 00:19:36,107
pain itself, and not the disease.

281
00:19:38,507 --> 00:19:43,117
Don't you want to know
what that is?

282
00:19:45,647 --> 00:19:46,857
Show him.

283
00:19:56,037 --> 00:19:56,847
Hi.

284
00:20:00,217 --> 00:20:02,257
Excuse me, Ms. Chae.

285
00:20:02,257 --> 00:20:04,387
Do you need something?

286
00:20:04,387 --> 00:20:08,877
Is there a clinical trial for
patients with terminal cancer?

287
