Actually, my sister received this
text on her phone yesterday.

288
00:20:16,817 --> 00:20:20,557
A presentation on a clinical trial
for terminal cancer patients.

289
00:20:20,557 --> 00:20:23,347
Please come to "Conversation about death"
at 5 p.m. tomorrow.

290
00:20:24,627 --> 00:20:26,707
"Conversation about death."

291
00:20:26,707 --> 00:20:28,947
Isn't this the meeting you
attended yesterday?

292
00:20:28,947 --> 00:20:31,207
"Conversation about death."

293
00:20:35,767 --> 00:20:38,067
[ Her brain waves started from beta
and transitioned to theta. ]

294
00:20:44,327 --> 00:20:46,507
[ Then it finally flatlined, and Ms. Park Hyun Sook
passed away peacefully. ]

295
00:20:48,077 --> 00:20:50,767
[ "Kerubim" promises an end without pain ]

296
00:20:53,457 --> 00:20:55,137
What do you think?

297
00:21:19,487 --> 00:21:21,307
Is this the police?

298
00:21:22,867 --> 00:21:25,867
There's a murderer here.

299
00:21:25,877 --> 00:21:28,847
Conspiring to murder and murder.

300
00:21:28,847 --> 00:21:30,777
He's guilty of it all.

301
00:21:31,907 --> 00:21:33,417
What if I report to the police

302
00:21:33,417 --> 00:21:35,167
after you kill my patient?

303
00:21:35,167 --> 00:21:38,417
Why would you show this to me?

304
00:21:40,327 --> 00:21:42,627
Mur... murder?

305
00:21:42,627 --> 00:21:45,227
Or will you call it
"salvation" instead?

306
00:21:45,227 --> 00:21:47,317
Salvation...

307
00:21:48,917 --> 00:21:53,357
What is the big deal
about "death"?

308
00:21:53,357 --> 00:21:56,187
Everyone dies.

309
00:21:56,187 --> 00:21:59,157
However, not everyone can

310
00:21:59,157 --> 00:22:02,117
experience a peaceful death.

311
00:22:02,117 --> 00:22:04,427
Death, which is...

312
00:22:04,427 --> 00:22:07,187
unavoidable for everyone...

313
00:22:07,187 --> 00:22:12,087
What is so bad about
wanting to go pleasantly?

314
00:22:17,167 --> 00:22:19,117
In one hand...

315
00:22:19,117 --> 00:22:21,917
you have a tormented patient.

316
00:22:21,917 --> 00:22:26,597
If you were given this drug
in your other hand...

317
00:22:28,597 --> 00:22:31,987
what kind of choice
would you make?

318
00:22:41,667 --> 00:22:43,327
[ Prosecutor, Yu Ri Hye
received this text ]

319
00:22:43,367 --> 00:22:44,667
[ "A presentation regarding a clinical trial
for terminal cancer patients." ]

320
00:22:46,867 --> 00:22:48,767
[ Chae Eun Jung ]

321
00:22:52,317 --> 00:22:54,107
Yu Ri Hye received this text?

322
00:22:54,167 --> 00:22:54,867
Yes.

323
00:22:54,867 --> 00:22:55,967
Something's off, right?

324
00:22:55,997 --> 00:22:59,447
They never gather clinical
trial participants this way.

325
00:22:59,447 --> 00:23:00,427
When did she receive it?

326
00:23:00,427 --> 00:23:01,587
Yesterday.

327
00:23:01,587 --> 00:23:02,857
Then it's today.

328
00:23:06,327 --> 00:23:08,167
Dr. Cha, don't go.

329
00:23:08,167 --> 00:23:09,507
We have more to talk about.

330
00:23:09,507 --> 00:23:10,547
Dr. Cha.

331
00:23:12,207 --> 00:23:13,427
This was it?

332
00:23:13,467 --> 00:23:15,967
Use me to legalize
euthanasia and sell that drug?

333
00:23:15,997 --> 00:23:17,517
I also have the same illness!

334
00:23:18,897 --> 00:23:21,477
I have the same illness
as the minister.

335
00:23:23,047 --> 00:23:25,327
The disease which traps
me in my body.

336
00:23:25,327 --> 00:23:28,147
My mind is sound,
but my body will die.

337
00:23:29,787 --> 00:23:31,817
For patients like me...

338
00:23:31,817 --> 00:23:34,117
that drug is our only hope.

339
00:23:35,447 --> 00:23:36,797
Myung Oh.

340
00:23:38,927 --> 00:23:42,007
Myung Oh, come to
your senses and listen.

341
00:23:42,007 --> 00:23:43,057
Okay?

342
00:23:43,057 --> 00:23:45,917
This is different from euthanasia.

343
00:23:45,917 --> 00:23:47,527
Will that drug be

344
00:23:47,527 --> 00:23:49,917
given only to doctors
and patients in need?

345
00:23:49,917 --> 00:23:52,367
Anyone can die,
and anyone can kill.

346
00:23:52,367 --> 00:23:54,917
No one will try to save
or cure anymore.

347
00:23:56,377 --> 00:23:58,007
I wanted to help...

348
00:24:00,067 --> 00:24:02,037
patients like me.

349
00:24:03,987 --> 00:24:05,777
I'm sorry about your illness.

350
00:24:07,067 --> 00:24:08,267
But...

351
00:24:09,267 --> 00:24:11,167
you weren't trying to
help the patients.

352
00:24:12,677 --> 00:24:15,357
You were only trying
to help yourself.

353
00:24:36,547 --> 00:24:37,607
Dr. Cha!

354
00:24:37,607 --> 00:24:39,897
Dr. Cha! My Ki Seok.

355
00:24:39,967 --> 00:24:40,967
Please save him.

356
00:24:40,967 --> 00:24:42,767
- Dad!
- Honey...

357
00:24:42,827 --> 00:24:46,227
What is the big deal about "death"?

358
00:24:46,227 --> 00:24:47,337
Mom...

359
00:24:47,337 --> 00:24:49,017
You suffered so much.

360
00:24:49,017 --> 00:24:51,447
I love you, Mom.

361
00:24:51,447 --> 00:24:53,187
It hurts.

362
00:24:53,267 --> 00:24:55,567
It hurts so much.

363
00:24:55,567 --> 00:24:56,467
Please stop.

364
00:24:57,467 --> 00:24:59,567
Dad is in a lot of pain.

365
00:24:59,597 --> 00:25:01,347
Speeding up death for relief and

366
00:25:01,367 --> 00:25:03,467
speeding up death to
take a life is different!

367
00:25:03,467 --> 00:25:04,687
I'm not...

368
00:25:05,427 --> 00:25:08,167
a doctor who takes away lives.

369
00:25:09,167 --> 00:25:10,627
Please save me.

370
00:25:11,567 --> 00:25:13,667
Dr. Cha, I want to live.

371
00:25:15,137 --> 00:25:17,797
Do you know what "death" is?

372
00:25:20,997 --> 00:25:24,687
When they're forgotten
by their loved ones.

373
00:25:58,297 --> 00:25:59,717
Minister.

374
00:26:02,787 --> 00:26:05,167
Make the preparations.

375
00:26:06,537 --> 00:26:10,957
And call the doctor as well.

376
00:26:10,957 --> 00:26:12,457
Yes, sir.

377
00:26:12,457 --> 00:26:14,177
I will.

378
00:26:15,837 --> 00:26:17,607
At "Conversation about death"?

379
00:26:17,607 --> 00:26:19,807
If an incident like the
Kerubim video happens,

380
00:26:19,867 --> 00:26:22,867
then "Conversation about death"
could become a murder site.

381
00:26:23,967 --> 00:26:26,667
Shall we get going?
There's not much time.

382
00:26:30,987 --> 00:26:31,767
[ Cha Yo Han ]

383
00:26:31,777 --> 00:26:33,127
[ Seongbukgu Seongbukdong 127 ]

384
00:26:33,717 --> 00:26:36,977
Seongbukgu Seongbukdong 127?

385
00:26:36,977 --> 00:26:39,607
It's former Minister
Lee Won Gil's address.

386
00:26:54,047 --> 00:26:55,137
What is this?

387
00:26:55,137 --> 00:26:57,377
I said it's former
Minister Lee Won Gil's address.

388
00:26:57,377 --> 00:26:59,117
So why are you giving it to me...

389
00:26:59,117 --> 00:27:00,857
Do you know anything?

390
00:27:00,857 --> 00:27:03,557
You mentioned something
about a drug before.

391
00:27:04,787 --> 00:27:05,997
What if...

392
00:27:05,997 --> 00:27:09,597
there was a drug which allowed
for a pleasant, peaceful death?

393
00:27:09,597 --> 00:27:10,767
Kerubim.

394
00:27:11,957 --> 00:27:13,287
Did you see the clip?

395
00:27:13,287 --> 00:27:14,107
Yes.

396
00:27:14,967 --> 00:27:17,167
- You knew about that drug, correct?
- Yes.

397
00:27:17,167 --> 00:27:18,167
So...

398
00:27:18,167 --> 00:27:21,267
how is Kerubim connected to the
former Minister Lee Won Gil?

399
00:27:21,297 --> 00:27:24,867
Former Minister Lee Won Gil
showed me that video clip,

400
00:27:24,867 --> 00:27:28,137
and location in question
was his house.

401
00:27:29,737 --> 00:27:31,967
This is enough to
charge him, correct?

402
00:27:31,967 --> 00:27:34,757
- Arrest him quickly.
- Why me?

403
00:27:36,557 --> 00:27:39,007
I said, why are you telling me this?

404
00:27:39,007 --> 00:27:41,397
Considering who the opponent is,

405
00:27:41,397 --> 00:27:43,417
I needed someone
who'll investigate

406
00:27:43,417 --> 00:27:46,257
tenaciously and not succumb
to any outside pressure.

407
00:27:46,257 --> 00:27:48,097
Please use...

408
00:27:48,097 --> 00:27:51,167
your tenacity for these
instances, not on me.

409
00:27:58,687 --> 00:28:01,067
We have an emergency.
We'll split up into two teams.

410
00:28:01,067 --> 00:28:02,687
I got a tip that the Kerubim video

411
00:28:02,767 --> 00:28:04,367
was viewed at former
Minister Lee Won Gil's house.

412
00:28:04,367 --> 00:28:05,367
We'll go to the minister's house.

413
00:28:05,407 --> 00:28:07,367
You go to the "Conversation about death."
Call the local police for backup.

414
00:28:07,367 --> 00:28:08,267
Yes, sir.

415
00:28:08,277 --> 00:28:09,577
But Prosecutor.

416
00:28:09,577 --> 00:28:12,167
Who tipped you off?

417
00:28:13,107 --> 00:28:15,057
- That's confidential.
- Pardon?

418
00:28:15,057 --> 00:28:16,387
I must protect the informant.

419
00:28:16,387 --> 00:28:17,557
Let's get going.

420
00:28:24,367 --> 00:28:26,447
I understand.

421
00:28:27,837 --> 00:28:31,557
Please take care of the aftermath.

422
00:28:31,557 --> 00:28:33,307
Doctor.

423
00:28:33,307 --> 00:28:35,147
[ Doctor ]

424
00:28:57,037 --> 00:29:02,727
Death washes away
all pain and sorrow.

425
00:29:02,727 --> 00:29:05,907
It's a magnificent grace.

426
00:29:08,867 --> 00:29:11,867
Farewell...

427
00:29:27,967 --> 00:29:30,867
[ Kerubim ]

428
00:29:50,667 --> 00:29:52,067
I don't hear anyone.

429
00:30:05,097 --> 00:30:07,057
Stand by until I call for you.

430
00:30:07,057 --> 00:30:07,857
Yes, sir.

431
00:30:38,617 --> 00:30:40,187
He's dead.

432
00:30:42,587 --> 00:30:43,977
[ Kerubim ]

